1. Binance HODLer will list Berachain (BERA) and provide airdrop rewards;
2. The X account of former Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad was hacked to release false token information;
3. Meme project PAIN: 185,976 SOLs were raised in pre-sale, and 80% of the funds raised will be refunded;
4. Standard Chartered: Bitcoin price may rise to $500,000 before Trump leaves office;
5. The US FDIC is re-evaluating the regulation of cryptocurrency activities, and the original regulatory warning has been deleted;
6. The US SEC transferred the crypto litigation lawyers involved in the Ripple and Coinbase cases to the IT department;
7. Musk supports putting US Treasury transactions on the chain;
8. Strategy announced that the annual "BTC income" target for 2025 is US$10 billion;
9. US Treasury Secretary Bessant: Trump did not call on the Fed to lower interest rates;
10. Berachain announced the economics of tokens: a total of 500 million, and the proportion of airdrops 15.8%;
11. Token trading infrastructure Reservoir completed a $14 million Series A financing, led by USV;
12. 0G Foundation launched an ecosystem fund of $88.88 million;
13. The New York Stock Exchange applied to convert the Grayscale LTC Trust Fund into a spot ETF;
14. Goldman Sachs and Wells Fargo expect the Federal Reserve to cut interest rates twice this year;
15. Cboe BZX Exchange plans to launch Ethereum spot ETF options trading;
16. The US SEC has transferred crypto litigation lawyer Jorge Tenreiro to the IT department.
